{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"2\n    \n      One Adaptive UI (progressive unlock)\n      No persona gate. First visit = minimal canvas with one big CTA: \"Try Singleton →\". UI unlocks progressively as user completes walkthroughs. Advanced tools (Mermaid editor, SOLID spotter, code generator) appear after milestones. Same URL throughout.\n\n      \n      \n        PROGRESSIVE UNLOCK — same URL, UI grows\n        \n          \n            ▸ NEW USER\n            \n            \"Try Singleton →\"\n          \n          \n            ▸ 3 PATTERNS DONE\n            \n            \n              \n              \n            \n            \n          \n          \n            ▸ ADVANCED\n            \n            \n              \n              \n              \n            \n            \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Zero onboarding friction — start fast\n            Single UI = single codebase to maintain\n            Feels magical — \"app grew up with me\"\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Crammer (persona C) hates unlocks — wants full power now\n            Progress-gating = frustrating if it gates wrong\n            Hard to serve D's \"I know this, skip me ahead\"\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        Effort: 🟡 Medium (3-4 weeks) · Risk: High (UX design risk) · Future flex: Medium","choice":"2","id":null,"timestamp":1776637842961}
