{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Progressive reveal · wrong answers become teachable moments\n      Each wrong answer gets a targeted explanation (data already exists in quizQuestions.options[].whyWrong). After 3 attempts, reveal correct answer + full explanation. User can always skip voluntarily — no forced gate.\n\n      \n        \n          Attempt 1 — wrong\n          \"Not quite. Here's why that's not right: [whyWrong text for that option]. Try again?\"\n        \n        \n          Attempt 2 — wrong\n          \"Still off. Consider: [hint text]. One more shot or [Reveal answer].\"\n        \n        \n          Attempt 3 — wrong or reveal clicked\n          \"The answer is B. Reason: [full explanation]. [Next section →]\"\n        \n        \n          ✓ Correct any time\n          \"Correct. [Full explanation so you know why]. [Next →]\"\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Failure becomes teaching. Never hostile. whyWrong data already seeded in DB. FSRS gets good signal (1 attempt vs 3 attempts = different retention score).\n        Cons: Content cost — need quality whyWrong for every option (Claude Opus writes these).","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776640206470}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/14-q04-graduation.html"}
{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/14-q04-graduation.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      3-tier · Introduced → Completed → Mastered · with decay\n      Three visible levels. Mastered decays back to Completed if no FSRS review passes in 90+ days — motivates ongoing review without punishing absence.\n\n      \n        ○  Singleton — not started\n        ◐  Factory Method — Introduced\n        ◉  Builder — Completed\n        ★  Observer — Mastered\n        ◉  Strategy — lapsing, review due\n      \n\n      \n      \n        \n          ◐ Introduced:\n           ≥50% scroll depth OR 1+ checkpoint attempted\n        \n        \n          ◉ Completed:\n           100% scroll + ≥70% checkpoints correct (reveals count as wrong)\n        \n        \n          ★ Mastered:\n           Completed + drill passed (≥70% grade) + 1+ FSRS review retained\n        \n        \n          📉 Lapsing (not a tier, a warning):\n           Completed/Mastered + FSRS says review is overdue (stability low). Shown separately.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Maps cleanly to 3 icon glyphs. Motivates both first-time completion and long-term retention. Drill integration baked in. FSRS lapsing surfaces as actionable nudge.\n        Cons: Needs 3 signals (scroll, drill, FSRS) to compute — slightly more DB reads. Manageable.","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776640341138}
