{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      4th primary mode · \"Review\"\n      Add a 4th pill to the switcher. Review lives alongside Learn/Build/Drill. Badge shows \"N due\" count in real-time.\n\n      \n        SWITCHER (top chrome)\n        \n          📖 Learn\n          🎨 Build\n          ⏱️ Drill\n          \n            🔁 Review\n            3\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        REVIEW MODE LAYOUT · minimal, distraction-free\n        \n          \n            \n              \n            \n            1 of 3 · Singleton\n          \n          Quick question:\n          Why is Singleton's constructor typically made private?\n          \n            A · To save memory\n            B · To prevent external new calls\n            C · Convention\n          \n          \n            Skip\n            Open in Learn →\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Review is visible → builds habit. Badge makes it feel like a task. Clean separation. Minimal layout = phone-friendly daily driver.\n        Cons: 4 modes > 3 modes. Slightly more UI complexity.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776640495045}
