{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/16-q06-mobile.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tiered support · be honest about what works where\n      Each mode gets the support level that matches its nature. Don't fake it.\n\n      \n        \n          🔁 Review · mobile-first\n           — optimized for phone. Big buttons, swipeable rating, vertical layout. This is the primary mobile experience.\n        \n        \n          📖 Learn · responsive\n           — full 3-col on desktop, stacked vertical on mobile. Canvas becomes an inline diagram card embedded between lesson sections (not a sticky panel). Scroll-sync replaced with \"tap to zoom\". Checkpoints always inline.\n        \n        \n          ⏱️ Drill · read-only on mobile\n           — mobile shows drill history + problem catalog + \"Solve on desktop\" CTA with email-link. Active drilling is desktop/tablet only. (Tablet drill works OK — stylus on iPad is viable.)\n        \n        \n          🎨 Build · desktop-only with honest fallback\n           — on mobile, show a preview of user's saved diagrams + message: \"Build mode needs desktop for precise UML editing. Open on laptop?\" + email-yourself-a-link button.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Each mode gets the right treatment. Review becomes a habit-forming mobile daily driver. Learn works on commute. No apology for Build being desktop — pros respect tool honesty.\n        Cons: Multiple layouts per mode. ~10-15h extra over desktop-only.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776640704542}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tiered support · be honest about what works where\n      Each mode gets the support level that matches its nature. Don't fake it.\n\n      \n        \n          🔁 Review · mobile-first\n           — optimized for phone. Big buttons, swipeable rating, vertical layout. This is the primary mobile experience.\n        \n        \n          📖 Learn · responsive\n           — full 3-col on desktop, stacked vertical on mobile. Canvas becomes an inline diagram card embedded between lesson sections (not a sticky panel). Scroll-sync replaced with \"tap to zoom\". Checkpoints always inline.\n        \n        \n          ⏱️ Drill · read-only on mobile\n           — mobile shows drill history + problem catalog + \"Solve on desktop\" CTA with email-link. Active drilling is desktop/tablet only. (Tablet drill works OK — stylus on iPad is viable.)\n        \n        \n          🎨 Build · desktop-only with honest fallback\n           — on mobile, show a preview of user's saved diagrams + message: \"Build mode needs desktop for precise UML editing. Open on laptop?\" + email-yourself-a-link button.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Each mode gets the right treatment. Review becomes a habit-forming mobile daily driver. Learn works on commute. No apology for Build being desktop — pros respect tool honesty.\n        Cons: Multiple layouts per mode. ~10-15h extra over desktop-only.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776640744304}
