{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/18-q08-tinker.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tinker mode · temporary unlock with reset & fork-to-Build\n      Small \"✏️ Tinker\" button floats above canvas in Learn mode. Click → canvas becomes editable. Scroll-sync pauses. A persistent toolbar appears with [Reset to lesson] [Save to Build] [Done tinkering].\n\n      \n      \n        \n          \n          \n            \n              ✏️\n              Tinkering\n              · scroll-sync paused\n            \n            \n            ↺ Reset to lesson\n            💾 Save to Build\n            ✓ Done\n          \n          \n          \n            Creator\n            Product\n            \n              ProductC\n              (user-added)\n            \n          \n          \n            User dragged out a new ProductC class. Lesson scroll is paused until they click \"Done\" or \"Reset\".\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        Done tinkering — canvas animates back to lesson state, scroll-sync resumes. Tinker session discarded.\n        Reset to lesson — immediate revert without leaving tinker mode. Like CMD+Z for the whole session.\n        Save to Build — takes tinker state, opens Build mode with it as a new named scratch. Switch modes explicit.\n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Serves productive-failure learners. Never destroys curated lesson. Save-to-Build = natural bridge. Mode remains Learn but with a pause state — no state confusion.\n        Cons: Adds a \"tinkering\" sub-state to Learn mode. UX complexity: scroll-sync paused needs a visual indicator.","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776641426440}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/19-q09-ai-in-learn.html"}
