{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tiered reveal · celebration scales to earned quality\n      3-second choreography: grading spinner → score emerges → breakdown unfolds → action choices. Visual treatment varies by tier — confetti only when earned (≥90%), specific coaching when failing. Never brutal, never infantilizing.\n\n      \n      \n\n        \n        \n          \n            \n              95\n            \n            \n              ⭐ Excellent — interview-ready\n              Parking Lot · 24:12 · 0 hints used\n            \n            🎉\n          \n          Subtle confetti burst · streak increment · \"Pattern mastered\" badge if this is the 1st FSRS pass\n        \n\n        \n        \n          \n            \n              78\n            \n            \n              ✓ Solid · you nailed the core\n              Parking Lot · 28:41 · 1 hint used\n            \n          \n          No confetti. \"One thing to tune: cardinality on Spot-Vehicle relationship\" — specific coaching.\n        \n\n        \n        \n          \n            \n              60\n            \n            \n              ◐ Partial · close, not there\n              Parking Lot · 35:07 · 3 hints used\n            \n          \n          \"Missing: Payment class. Weak: Spot-Level relationship. Consider reviewing State pattern before retrying.\"\n        \n\n        \n        \n          \n            \n              40\n            \n            \n              ○ Keep going · this one's tough\n              Parking Lot · 41:22 · gave up\n            \n          \n          \"Parking Lot is medium-hard. Step back — try Learn mode for State + Factory patterns first, come back stronger.\"\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        ALWAYS SHOW · 4-category breakdown (collapsible per-category)\n        \n          Classes 32/40\n          Relations 21/30\n          Pattern 18/20\n          Complete 7/10\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        Next-action row (tiered): 90+ shows \"Next problem →\"; 70-89 shows \"Retry · Next problem\"; 50-69 shows \"Review this pattern · Retry\"; <50 shows \"Open Learn mode · See reference solution\".\n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Celebration is earned. Failure is coached. Pros get specifics, beginners get paths forward. 3-second choreography feels intentional, not patronizing.\n        Cons: More component surface (4 tiered reveals vs 1 generic). ~5-8h extra.","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776641710202}
