{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/24-q14-keyboard.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Global shortcuts + mode vocabulary + palette fallback\n      Three tiers: global (always work), mode-specific (contextual, respect input focus), palette (the discovery + fallback for unmemorized actions).\n\n      \n      \n        GLOBAL · WORK EVERYWHERE\n        \n          ⌘1 Learn mode    ⌘2 Build    ⌘3 Drill    ⌘4 Review\n          ⌘K Command palette    ⌘/ Shortcuts help    Esc Close modal\n        \n      \n\n      \n        📖 LEARN MODE\n        \n          J/K Scroll sections    ←/→ Prev / next pattern\n          1..4 Answer checkpoint option A/B/C/D    Enter Submit\n          T Toggle Tinker mode    ? Ask the Architect\n        \n      \n\n      \n        🎨 BUILD MODE\n        \n          # via existing useKeyboardNodeOps + new:\n          N New class    E Edit selected    Del Delete\n          ⌘Z / ⌘⇧Z Undo / redo    ⌘S Save as diagram\n          F Fit to view    M Toggle minimap\n        \n      \n\n      \n        ⏱️ DRILL MODE\n        \n          Space Pause/resume timer    H Open hint panel\n          ⌘Enter Submit (with confirm)    ⌘G Give up (with confirm)\n          R Show requirements    [  ] Prev / next problem in queue\n        \n      \n\n      \n        🔁 REVIEW MODE · speed-optimized · Anki-inspired\n        \n          1..4 Answer option A/B/C/D    Space Reveal answer\n          A / H / G / E Rate FSRS: Again / Hard / Good / Easy\n          Enter Next review item    Esc Exit session\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          Discovery: Pressing ? in any mode shows a mode-specific shortcuts overlay. Palette remains the \"search any action\" fallback for unmemorized shortcuts.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Review mode runs at Anki speed (critical for daily habit). Drill pros submit with ⌘Enter. Palette still handles the long tail. Mode-specific means no conflicts (J in Learn = scroll; J in Build could mean something else — not collision).\n        Cons: Memorization burden. ? overlay mitigates. Existing hooks do most of the work — new code ≈ 8h for Review shortcuts + Drill shortcuts.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776642499024}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/25-q15-frustration.html"}
{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/25-q15-frustration.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Escalating · 4 levels of increasing help\n      Detector level → intervention. Each level does more. User can dismiss any level to de-escalate back.\n\n      \n\n        \n        \n          🟦 Calm (score < 8)\n          No intervention. Detector logs for analytics.\n        \n\n        \n        \n          🟩 Mild (8-17)\n          \n            Gentle inline prompt at bottom of lesson column: \"Taking your time on this one. Want a nudge? [Hint]\". Dismissable. One-time per section.\n          \n        \n\n        \n        \n          🟨 Frustrated (18-29)\n          \n            Pro-active help offer: floating assistant appears bottom-right: \"I see you're working through this. Want me to explain the tricky part? [Yes, explain] [I've got it]\". AI opens pre-loaded with current section context.\n          \n        \n\n        \n        \n          🟥 Very Frustrated (30+)\n          \n            Permission-asking pattern. Full-pane but dismissable card: \"This pattern's tricky. A few options:\"\n            [Jump to section summary] · [Try an easier pattern first (we'll suggest one)] · [Take a break · come back later] · [Keep going]\n            No shame. Never blocks. Reverse-recommend path based on prerequisite DAG.\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        PER-MODE NUANCES\n        \n          📖 Learn: interventions above · all levels active\n          🎨 Build: only mild-level nudge appropriate · \"Stuck designing? Try a template.\" Pros shouldn't be interrupted.\n          ⏱️ Drill: NEVER intervene mid-drill — simulating interview means no safety net. Post-submit, if they failed 2+ times and frustration was high, show the very-frustrated card.\n          🔁 Review: high rating variance only. \"Struggling on Observer? [Jump to Learn mode for Observer]\"\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Uses existing infrastructure. Matches intensity to need. Drill respects interview realism. Very-frustrated card reduces churn on hard patterns.\n        Cons: 4-level state machine to get right. Tuning scores matters. ≈ 10h including QA.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776642590536}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/26-q16-loading.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tiered prefetch · instant + warm + cold\n      Three tiers based on likely access:\n\n      \n\n        \n          ① INSTANT · 5 foundation patterns in initial bundle\n          \n            Singleton · Factory Method · Observer · Strategy · Builder — the 5 first-wave patterns most users open first. Shipped with initial JS bundle. ~225 KB gz. Zero API call for the first 5 experiences — critical for first-impression perf.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ② WARM · next 10 prefetched on idle\n          \n            After initial page load, requestIdleCallback kicks off background fetches for next 10 patterns (wave 1 remaining + wave 2 start). User clicks → already in TanStack Query cache = 0ms. Invisible prefetch.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ③ COLD · remaining 21 on-demand\n          \n            Rare patterns (AI-Agent, Concurrency, advanced modern) fetched only when clicked. 200-400ms fetch on click. Loading skeleton during. TanStack Query caches for 30min.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ④ OFFLINE · service worker for everything accessed\n          \n            Service worker caches every fetched pattern. Re-opening an already-seen pattern = offline-capable. PWA-ready for commute reading.\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        ADAPTIVE PREFETCH\n        \n          // On idle, prefetch based on user context:\n          if (userProgress.completedPatternCount >= 3) {\n            // Prefetch next pattern in path\n            prefetchPattern(getNextInPath(userProgress));\n          }\n          if (hovering(patternTile)) {\n            // Hover-prefetch — pattern loads before click\n            prefetchPattern(hovered.slug);\n          }\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: First 5 patterns instant (covers 80% of users' first week). Adaptive prefetch = \"next\" patterns warm when users reach them. Hover-prefetch catches the remaining. Offline + PWA as free bonus from service worker. Bundle size cut by 75%+.\n        Cons: More orchestration. TanStack Query config + service worker + prefetch hooks. ~8-10h extra.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776642695333}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Tiered prefetch · instant + warm + cold\n      Three tiers based on likely access:\n\n      \n\n        \n          ① INSTANT · 5 foundation patterns in initial bundle\n          \n            Singleton · Factory Method · Observer · Strategy · Builder — the 5 first-wave patterns most users open first. Shipped with initial JS bundle. ~225 KB gz. Zero API call for the first 5 experiences — critical for first-impression perf.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ② WARM · next 10 prefetched on idle\n          \n            After initial page load, requestIdleCallback kicks off background fetches for next 10 patterns (wave 1 remaining + wave 2 start). User clicks → already in TanStack Query cache = 0ms. Invisible prefetch.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ③ COLD · remaining 21 on-demand\n          \n            Rare patterns (AI-Agent, Concurrency, advanced modern) fetched only when clicked. 200-400ms fetch on click. Loading skeleton during. TanStack Query caches for 30min.\n          \n        \n\n        \n          ④ OFFLINE · service worker for everything accessed\n          \n            Service worker caches every fetched pattern. Re-opening an already-seen pattern = offline-capable. PWA-ready for commute reading.\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        ADAPTIVE PREFETCH\n        \n          // On idle, prefetch based on user context:\n          if (userProgress.completedPatternCount >= 3) {\n            // Prefetch next pattern in path\n            prefetchPattern(getNextInPath(userProgress));\n          }\n          if (hovering(patternTile)) {\n            // Hover-prefetch — pattern loads before click\n            prefetchPattern(hovered.slug);\n          }\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: First 5 patterns instant (covers 80% of users' first week). Adaptive prefetch = \"next\" patterns warm when users reach them. Hover-prefetch catches the remaining. Offline + PWA as free bonus from service worker. Bundle size cut by 75%+.\n        Cons: More orchestration. TanStack Query config + service worker + prefetch hooks. ~8-10h extra.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776642724139}
