{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Light social · shareable grade cards + optional public profile\n      Three surfaces, no leaderboards, no competition:\n\n      \n      \n        ① DRILL SHARE CARDS · dynamic OG image on ⭐ 90+ grade\n\n        \n        \n          \n            \n              95\n            \n            \n              Designed Parking Lot in 24:12\n              on Architex · 18 classes · 0 hints used\n              \n                Factory Method\n                State\n                Singleton\n              \n            \n            ⭐\n          \n          architex.app\n        \n        Server-rendered OG image (Next.js /api/og already exists). Previews in Twitter/LinkedIn/Slack as a rich card. Tap → open drill problem page.\n      \n\n      \n      \n        ② OPTIONAL PUBLIC PROFILE · /profile/[username]\n        \n          Off by default. Settings toggle: \"Make my profile public\". If on: shows patterns mastered count, streak, achievements, drill pass rate. Never shows individual drill scores (just aggregate). Username customizable. Linkable from LinkedIn.\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        ③ DIAGRAM SHARE · existing gallery mechanism\n        \n          Already exists: gallerySubmissions table. From Build mode, \"Share to gallery\" posts a named diagram publicly. OG card generated per-diagram. Already-built infrastructure.\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        DEFERRED TO V2 · explicitly not in scope\n        \n          ❌ Leaderboards (global rankings, friends rankings) · ❌ Multiplayer battles (1v1) · ❌ Comments on shared diagrams · ❌ Follow-other-users · ❌ Public drill history\n          These are P2 innovation features — build when user base supports it.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Viral growth vehicle (OG cards). LinkedIn-shareable profile = career marketing for users. Reuses existing /api/og + gallerySubmissions. No moderation overhead (no comments, no DMs). Excellent effort/return ratio.\n        Cons: Share card design takes polish iteration. ~10h for 3 surfaces + dynamic OG.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776642937898}
