{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Full funnel · ~25 events with typed schema · dual-purpose\n      Typed event catalog. Each event writes to activityEvents (owned by user, drives personal stats) AND mirrors to PostHog (aggregate funnels).\n\n      \n      \n\n        📖 LEARN MODE (9)\n        \n          lld_pattern_opened {patternId, fromMode}\n          lld_scroll_milestone {patternId, depth: 25|50|75|100}\n          lld_checkpoint_attempted {patternId, checkpointId, attemptNumber, correct}\n          lld_checkpoint_revealed {patternId, checkpointId, attemptsBeforeReveal}\n          lld_section_completed {patternId, sectionId, timeSpentMs}\n          lld_pattern_completed {patternId, tier, durationMs}\n          lld_tinker_started / ended {patternId, saved: boolean}\n          lld_ai_invoked_in_learn {surface: \"failed_checkpoint\"|\"section_end\"|\"confused_with\"}\n          lld_frustration_level_changed {level, patternId}\n        \n\n        🎨 BUILD MODE (4)\n        \n          lld_build_canvas_modified {nodeCount, edgeCount, debounced 30s}\n          lld_build_ai_review_requested {issueCount, severity}\n          lld_build_diagram_saved {diagramId, classCount}\n          lld_build_diagram_exported {format: \"ts\"|\"py\"|\"java\"|\"mermaid\"}\n        \n\n        ⏱️ DRILL MODE (8)\n        \n          lld_drill_started {problemId, drillMode: interview|guided|speed}\n          lld_drill_paused {problemId, elapsedMs}\n          lld_drill_hint_used {tier, problemId, elapsedMs}\n          lld_drill_submitted {problemId, grade, breakdown, durationMs, hintsUsed}\n          lld_drill_abandoned {problemId, elapsedMs, reason: \"give_up\"|\"timeout\"|\"auto\"}\n          lld_drill_grade_tier_crossed {problemId, tier: excellent|solid|partial|needs_work}\n          lld_drill_canvas_heartbeat {drillId, elapsedMs, every 60s}\n          lld_drill_mode_switched_during {problemId, targetMode}\n        \n\n        🔁 REVIEW MODE (4)\n        \n          lld_review_session_started {dueCount}\n          lld_review_item_rated {patternId, fsrsRating: again|hard|good|easy, responseMs}\n          lld_review_session_completed {reviewCount, avgResponseMs, streakIncremented}\n          lld_review_abandoned_mid_session {completedCount, remaining}\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        CROSS-CUTTING EVENTS\n        \n          lld_mode_switched {from, to, trigger: click|keyboard|url}\n          lld_welcome_banner_shown / dismissed\n          lld_nudge_triggered / dismissed {nudgeType}\n          lld_anon_migration {case: 1|2|3, merged: patternCount}\n          lld_share_card_generated {type: drill|diagram|profile}\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        CRITICAL FUNNELS THIS ENABLES\n        \n          • Learn completion funnel: opened → scroll 25% → scroll 75% → all checkpoints → completed\n          • Learn → Drill conversion: completed pattern → drill started on same pattern\n          • Drill success funnel: started → hint used → submitted → graded ≥ 70\n          • Review retention: session started → rated item → session completed\n          • Learn → Mastered: opened → completed → drill pass → FSRS review → Mastered tier\n          • Abandonment signals: which step users drop at, which patterns are abandoned most\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Every meaningful action captured. Dual-purpose (product + user dashboard). Reuses existing activityEvents — no new schema. TypeScript-typed event builders prevent drift. Each event < 1 KB so log size is fine.\n        Cons: 25 events = 25 call sites to wire. ~6-8h for full instrumentation.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776643037723}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Full funnel · ~25 events with typed schema · dual-purpose\n      Typed event catalog. Each event writes to activityEvents (owned by user, drives personal stats) AND mirrors to PostHog (aggregate funnels).\n\n      \n      \n\n        📖 LEARN MODE (9)\n        \n          lld_pattern_opened {patternId, fromMode}\n          lld_scroll_milestone {patternId, depth: 25|50|75|100}\n          lld_checkpoint_attempted {patternId, checkpointId, attemptNumber, correct}\n          lld_checkpoint_revealed {patternId, checkpointId, attemptsBeforeReveal}\n          lld_section_completed {patternId, sectionId, timeSpentMs}\n          lld_pattern_completed {patternId, tier, durationMs}\n          lld_tinker_started / ended {patternId, saved: boolean}\n          lld_ai_invoked_in_learn {surface: \"failed_checkpoint\"|\"section_end\"|\"confused_with\"}\n          lld_frustration_level_changed {level, patternId}\n        \n\n        🎨 BUILD MODE (4)\n        \n          lld_build_canvas_modified {nodeCount, edgeCount, debounced 30s}\n          lld_build_ai_review_requested {issueCount, severity}\n          lld_build_diagram_saved {diagramId, classCount}\n          lld_build_diagram_exported {format: \"ts\"|\"py\"|\"java\"|\"mermaid\"}\n        \n\n        ⏱️ DRILL MODE (8)\n        \n          lld_drill_started {problemId, drillMode: interview|guided|speed}\n          lld_drill_paused {problemId, elapsedMs}\n          lld_drill_hint_used {tier, problemId, elapsedMs}\n          lld_drill_submitted {problemId, grade, breakdown, durationMs, hintsUsed}\n          lld_drill_abandoned {problemId, elapsedMs, reason: \"give_up\"|\"timeout\"|\"auto\"}\n          lld_drill_grade_tier_crossed {problemId, tier: excellent|solid|partial|needs_work}\n          lld_drill_canvas_heartbeat {drillId, elapsedMs, every 60s}\n          lld_drill_mode_switched_during {problemId, targetMode}\n        \n\n        🔁 REVIEW MODE (4)\n        \n          lld_review_session_started {dueCount}\n          lld_review_item_rated {patternId, fsrsRating: again|hard|good|easy, responseMs}\n          lld_review_session_completed {reviewCount, avgResponseMs, streakIncremented}\n          lld_review_abandoned_mid_session {completedCount, remaining}\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        CROSS-CUTTING EVENTS\n        \n          lld_mode_switched {from, to, trigger: click|keyboard|url}\n          lld_welcome_banner_shown / dismissed\n          lld_nudge_triggered / dismissed {nudgeType}\n          lld_anon_migration {case: 1|2|3, merged: patternCount}\n          lld_share_card_generated {type: drill|diagram|profile}\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        CRITICAL FUNNELS THIS ENABLES\n        \n          • Learn completion funnel: opened → scroll 25% → scroll 75% → all checkpoints → completed\n          • Learn → Drill conversion: completed pattern → drill started on same pattern\n          • Drill success funnel: started → hint used → submitted → graded ≥ 70\n          • Review retention: session started → rated item → session completed\n          • Learn → Mastered: opened → completed → drill pass → FSRS review → Mastered tier\n          • Abandonment signals: which step users drop at, which patterns are abandoned most\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Every meaningful action captured. Dual-purpose (product + user dashboard). Reuses existing activityEvents — no new schema. TypeScript-typed event builders prevent drift. Each event < 1 KB so log size is fine.\n        Cons: 25 events = 25 call sites to wire. ~6-8h for full instrumentation.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776643105399}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/30-q20-rollout.html"}
{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/30-q20-rollout.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      ⭐ MY RECOMMENDATION\n      Feature-flagged cohort rollout · phased ramp\n      Single codebase. lldV2Enabled flag. Cohort-gated rollout. Rollback via flag flip, no deploy.\n\n      \n      \n        \n\n          \n            \n              WAVE 1 · internal\n              Week 0 · ~5 users\n            \n            You + 2-4 teammates. Flag manually enabled for your user IDs. Stress-test all 4 modes, all edge cases from Q11 cross-mode table.\n          \n\n          \n            \n              WAVE 2 · alpha opt-in\n              Week 1 · ~50-100 users\n            \n            Banner in existing LLD: \"Try the new Learn/Build/Drill/Review experience? [Enable beta]\". Users opt-in. Feedback form prominent. Toggle to return to old UI anytime.\n          \n\n          \n            \n              WAVE 3 · anonymous 100%\n              Week 2-3 · new anonymous visitors\n            \n            All anonymous (logged-out) visitors get the new UI by default. No confused existing users. Monitor drill grade distribution, Review completion rate, churn signals.\n          \n\n          \n            \n              WAVE 4 · authenticated 10% → 50%\n              Week 4-5 · ramp gradually\n            \n            Hash userId → deterministic cohort. Start 10%, monitor metrics vs control. If healthy, ramp to 25%, 50%. Rollback = flip flag config, takes 30s.\n          \n\n          \n            \n              WAVE 5 · 100% + kill switch\n              Week 6+ · full rollout\n            \n            All users on new UI. Old code path stays for 4 more weeks behind a \"revert to old\" settings toggle (hidden) for anyone who really needs escape hatch. Then purge.\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        🚨 ROLLBACK TRIGGERS (auto-alert)\n        \n          • Drill submission error rate > 5%\n          • Learn pattern completion rate drops > 20% vs control cohort\n          • Mode switch bug causing data loss reports > 3 in 24h\n          • FSRS review rating distribution shifts suspiciously (e.g., 80% \"Again\" = review broken)\n          Hitting any of these → auto-flag revert + page on-call\n        \n      \n\n      \n      \n        FLAG IMPLEMENTATION\n        \n          // userPreferences.preferences.lld.v2Enabled || cohortRoll() || envOverride()\n          function isLLDV2Enabled(user) {\n            if (user?.preferences.lld.v2Optout) return false;\n            if (user?.preferences.lld.v2OptIn) return true;\n            if (!user) return ROLLOUT.anonymous;  // always true post-wave 3\n            return hashCohort(user.id) < ROLLOUT.authenticatedPercent;\n          }\n        \n      \n\n      \n        Pros: Safety at every step. Real user data informs ramp decisions. Rollback without deploy. 4 weeks of dual-path code is finite and bounded. Opt-in alpha generates testimonials + feedback. Existing users never get surprised.\n        Cons: 4-6 week rollout calendar. Dual UI paths exist briefly (shared shell minimizes this). Flag infrastructure needs to be reliable.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776643140346}
