{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V2\n    \n      Typography hierarchy upgrade in lesson column\n      Current lesson text is uniform 12-13px. Propose a narrative typography system for Learn mode: hook = 22px serif-ish display, analogy = italic soft 16px, section labels = 10px all-caps tracked, body = 14px, pull-quotes = large display on occasion. Creates reading rhythm like a great long-form article (NYT, The Atlantic).\n      \n        You're building a stock trading app.\n        THE HOOK\n        When a stock price changes, the dashboard, notifications, and portfolio all need to update.\n        Think of a newspaper subscription...\n      \n      Implementation: Tailwind typography extensions + lesson column-only CSS scope. ~5h.","choice":"v2","id":null,"timestamp":1776643703473}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V1\n    \n      Pattern-specific accent themes\n      Each pattern (or category) gets a signature micro-palette. Opening Singleton subtly shifts canvas background gradient + edge hue + header bar to a Singleton-specific color story. Creates a sense of place. Like moving between rooms.\n      \n        Creational · emerald\n        Structural · azure\n        Behavioral · violet\n        AI-Agent · fuchsia\n      \n      Implementation: CSS custom properties swap per pattern via data-attribute on shell. ~3h. Impact: high delight, zero functional change.","choice":"v1","id":null,"timestamp":1776643705329}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V3\n    \n      Canvas aesthetic variants · \"Paper / Whiteboard / Terminal\"\n      Settings toggle lets user swap canvas aesthetic — doesn't change UML semantics, changes the vibe:\n      \n        \n          📜 Paper\n          Sepia cream, hand-sketch edges (Excalidraw), brown ink\n        \n        \n          ⬜ Whiteboard\n          Stark white, blue marker edges, meeting-room feel\n        \n        \n          >_ Terminal\n          ASCII art style, monospace labels, green-on-black\n        \n      \n      Implementation: React Flow theme variants. ~10h for 2 new themes (Paper + Whiteboard). Terminal is \"fun but maybe v2\".","choice":"v3","id":null,"timestamp":1776643738956}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V3\n    \n      Canvas aesthetic variants · \"Paper / Whiteboard / Terminal\"\n      Settings toggle lets user swap canvas aesthetic — doesn't change UML semantics, changes the vibe:\n      \n        \n          📜 Paper\n          Sepia cream, hand-sketch edges (Excalidraw), brown ink\n        \n        \n          ⬜ Whiteboard\n          Stark white, blue marker edges, meeting-room feel\n        \n        \n          >_ Terminal\n          ASCII art style, monospace labels, green-on-black\n        \n      \n      Implementation: React Flow theme variants. ~10h for 2 new themes (Paper + Whiteboard). Terminal is \"fun but maybe v2\".","choice":"v3","id":null,"timestamp":1776643739980}
