{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V4\n    \n      Pattern mascot illustrations · the \"Architex Zoo\"\n      Each of the 36 patterns gets a bespoke small illustration (not stock icons) — a memorable visual cue. Singleton = lonely monk. Factory Method = assembly line worker. Observer = town crier. Mediator = traffic controller. Strategy = Swiss Army knife. Circuit Breaker = breaker panel.\n      \n        🧘\n        🏭\n        📢\n        🚦\n        🔧\n        ⚡\n        ...\n        (these are emoji placeholders — real illustrations would be line-art SVGs)\n      \n      Implementation: commission 36 SVG line-art illustrations (~$500-1500 Fiverr/dribbble) OR AI-generate 36 consistent illustrations (~$50 in Sonnet + editing, 6-8h human curation). The most viral identity feature you could ship.","choice":"v4","id":null,"timestamp":1776643748855}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V5\n    \n      \"Pressure palette\" · state colors during simulation\n      When Drill mode runs auto-grading, classes pulse with their evaluated state: missing = red outline, correct = green glow, partial = yellow. Currently classes look identical after grading. Visual semantic feedback at-a-glance.\n      \n        \n          ✓ Correct\n        \n        \n          ◐ Partial\n        \n        \n          ✗ Missing\n        \n      \n      Implementation: extend highlightedClassIds prop → classStates: {id, state}. Pulse via motion. ~6h.","choice":"v5","id":null,"timestamp":1776643755005}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V6\n    \n      Edge personality · protocol-style edge variants\n      Currently all UML edges are the same style (just marker differences). Propose: edges carry semantic style — inheritance = crisp solid, dependency = delicate dotted, data flow in runtime = animated dashed, weak reference = translucent. Turns edges from bookkeeping into storytelling.\n      Implementation: extend existing edge renderer. ~4h.","choice":"v6","id":null,"timestamp":1776643769701}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V7\n    \n      \"Reading mode\" overlay · distraction-free Learn\n      Shortcut toggles a full-screen reading overlay: fades sidebar + chrome + properties, expands lesson column to center 720px, increases font size 10%. Like Safari's Reader mode but for Learn mode. Perfect for deep focus reading.\n      Implementation: shell-level overlay class + hotkey binding. ~3h.","choice":"v7","id":null,"timestamp":1776643783484}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"V8\n    \n      Empty-state storytelling · \"Canvas is blank\" replaced\n      Currently empty canvas = \"Start Building\" + big icon. Replace with a randomized evocative prompt per visit: \"What kind of system keeps you up at night?\" · \"Designing for a million users? Start with one.\" · \"Every system begins with a single class.\" — rotating quotes that make the blank canvas feel inviting rather than intimidating.\n      Implementation: quote bank (20-30 curated) + random pick on mount. ~2h.","choice":"v8","id":null,"timestamp":1776643791734}
