{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/35-batch4-ai.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A1\n    \n      GitHub repo analysis · \"what patterns are you already using?\"\n      User connects a GitHub repo URL. Claude analyzes code, identifies which design patterns are already present, maps them to Architex's pattern catalog. Report: \"We found Singleton in src/db/connection.ts:L12, Observer in src/events/bus.ts:L45, potential Factory Method opportunity in src/parsers/ParserFactory.ts (currently switch statement).\" Learning feels personal, not abstract.\n      \n        ✓ Found: Singleton\n        db/pool.ts:L12 · thread-safe instance cache\n        ⚡ Opportunity: Strategy\n        payment/processor.ts:L23 · switch statement could be Strategy\n      \n      Costly per-call (Sonnet needed, ~10k tokens per repo). Throttle to Pro tier. ~20h build + $1-3/analysis in Claude cost. Viral demo material.","choice":"a1","id":null,"timestamp":1776644398202}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A2\n    \n      AI-generated custom scenarios · \"design a hotel booking system for Mars colonies\"\n      User types any scenario prompt → Claude generates a fresh LLD problem with requirements, starter classes, hints, reference solution. Infinite problem pool. Pro-tier feature. Users can save their custom problems, share them to gallery.\n      \n        PROMPT:\n        \"Design a restaurant order kitchen queue\"\n        CLAUDE OUTPUT (custom LLD problem):\n        6 requirements · 4 starter classes (Order, Kitchen, Chef, Ticket) · 5 progressive hints · uses: Observer (ticket status updates), Command (order execution), State (order lifecycle) · reference solution 12 classes\n      \n      Pro-tier. 1 generation = ~$0.05 in Claude Sonnet. Cap at 10/day free tier, unlimited Pro. ~12h build.","choice":"a2","id":null,"timestamp":1776644402690}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A3\n    \n      Socratic rubber duck · \"explain your design out loud, AI probes\"\n      After user builds in Drill mode, click \"Explain out loud\" → voice input (Whisper) or typed. Claude plays the interviewer, asks clarifying questions: \"Why did you choose composition over inheritance here?\" \"What happens if Payment fails mid-transaction?\" Tests your explanation skill — the actual interview skill, not just \"can you draw it\".\n      Claude Sonnet with architect persona (from existing socratic-tutor.ts). Whisper for voice. Can also use text. ~15h + voice stack.","choice":"a3","id":null,"timestamp":1776644417601}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A4\n    \n      Anti-pattern detector · live in Build mode\n      As user builds in Build mode, Claude watches (debounced 10s of inactivity). If the canvas has an anti-pattern — god class, deep inheritance, circular dependency — a subtle ⚠️ badge appears on the offending class. Click → Claude explains why it's an anti-pattern + suggests the refactor.\n      \n        \n          \n            GodClass\n            ⚠️\n          \n          37 methods detected — consider splitting by responsibility\n        \n      \n      Extends existing design-reviewer.ts. ~8h. Background analysis = Haiku (cheap, ~$0.002/check).","choice":"a4","id":null,"timestamp":1776644419717}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A5\n    \n      Pattern recommendation engine · \"you might want Strategy here\"\n      In Build mode, as user completes a recognizable shape (3+ classes implementing the same interface, a switch on type, etc.), Claude suggests: \"Your design suggests Strategy — want to preview how that'd reshape this?\" One click → shows a \"ghost preview\" of the refactored diagram.\n      Pattern-fingerprint heuristic first (fast, free) → Claude proposes specific pattern + preview (Sonnet). ~12h.","choice":"a5","id":null,"timestamp":1776644421001}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A6\n    \n      Personalized study plan · \"based on your weaknesses, here's 2 weeks\"\n      User clicks \"Generate study plan\" → provides goals (\"Meta interview in 3 weeks\"). Claude analyzes their FSRS data, Mastered tier patterns, drill results. Returns a day-by-day 2-week plan: \"Day 1: Learn Observer (30min). Day 2: Drill Parking Lot (30min). Day 3: Review flashcards (15min). ...\" Editable, trackable.\n      Leverages progress-store data + Claude synthesis. ~15h incl. calendar-like UI.","choice":"a6","id":null,"timestamp":1776644430792}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A7\n    \n      Company-style mock interviews · Amazon bar-raiser, Google leveling, Meta scope\n      Drill mode gets a preset: \"Interview Company\". Pick Amazon / Google / Meta / Stripe / Uber. Claude plays the interviewer with that company's known evaluation rubric — Amazon bar-raises for design simplicity, Google probes algorithmic complexity, Meta asks about scaling. Grade reflects company's specific bar.\n      Claude system prompts per-company (researched from Levels.fyi, Blind). ~10-12h + ongoing rubric refinement.","choice":"a7","id":null,"timestamp":1776644433502}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A8\n    \n      AI-translated code · your pattern in Go, Rust, Kotlin, Swift, C++ on demand\n      Pattern page has TS/Py/Java columns (from C7). Add a dropdown \"Translate to…\" → Claude generates idiomatic version in Go/Rust/Kotlin/Swift/C++/Elixir. Cached per pattern-language combo. Covers every language an engineer might work in.\n      On-demand generation, cached. 36 patterns × 6 extra languages if fully generated = 216 files (but lazy). ~8h infra.","choice":"a8","id":null,"timestamp":1776644439635}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A9\n    \n      AI flashcard generator · turn any lesson into Anki-style cards\n      After completing a lesson, one-click \"Generate flashcards\" → Claude creates 5-8 cards from that lesson's key concepts, formatted question/answer. Cards enter the FSRS review queue. Unlike templated flashcards, these are personalized per lesson content.\n      Haiku (cheap). Cached per lesson. ~6h.","choice":"a9","id":null,"timestamp":1776644441358}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/36-batch5-growth.html"}
{"type":"screen-updated","file":"/Users/a0g11b6/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-WalmartInc/Desktop/my_projects/architex/.superpowers/brainstorm/64431-1776636958/content/36-batch5-growth.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G1\n    \n      Embeddable widgets · iframe any pattern into a blog post\n      Every pattern page gets an \"Embed\" button → copy HTML snippet. Paste into Substack, Dev.to, personal blog. Readers see a live interactive UML preview, click through to Architex. Organic backlink network from dev blogs.\n      \n        <iframe src=\"architex.app/embed/pattern/singleton\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\">\n      \n      Already exists! src/app/embed/lld/pattern/[id]/page.tsx is built. Just need the \"copy embed\" button UI. ~3h.","choice":"g1","id":null,"timestamp":1776644550461}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G2\n    \n      Browser extension · pattern detector on any GitHub page\n      Install Architex browser extension. Browse any GitHub file. Extension highlights class definitions and silently labels them: \"Probable Singleton\", \"Factory Method\". Click label → opens that pattern's Architex lesson in new tab. Distribution via GitHub browsing behavior.\n      Chrome/Firefox MV3 extension. Haiku analysis per visible code block. ~30-40h for V1 + submission to stores.","choice":"g2","id":null,"timestamp":1776644554047}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G3\n    \n      VS Code extension · \"Explain this class's pattern\"\n      Right-click any class in VS Code → \"Explain via Architex\". Inline hover shows identified pattern + link to lesson. Pro tier: get anti-pattern warnings while coding. Embeds Architex into daily dev workflow.\n      VS Code LSP-style extension. Uses same AI + patterns data. ~40-60h for V1. Marketplace submission.","choice":"g3","id":null,"timestamp":1776644557138}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G4\n    \n      Completion certificates · LinkedIn-ready shareables\n      Complete all 5 creational patterns → unlock \"Creational Master\" certificate. Rendered as a clean OG-image certificate: name, date, pattern list, verification URL. One-click share to LinkedIn. Uses your existing /api/og infrastructure.\n      \n        ARCHITEX\n        Creational Patterns · Mastered\n        Anshul Garg · 2026-04-20\n        Singleton · Factory Method · Abstract Factory · Builder · Prototype\n      \n      8 certificates possible (8 waves × Mastered). ~6h template + cert verification URL backend.","choice":"g4","id":null,"timestamp":1776644559415}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G5\n    \n      Pattern of the Day · email subscription + RSS\n      Free opt-in. Every morning, a 3-min pattern deep-dive delivered by email or RSS. Cycles through 36 patterns every ~5 weeks. Same content as Learn mode but formatted for email skimming. Daily habit without requiring app open.\n      Resend integration (already in deps). Inngest scheduled job (already in stack). ~10h.","choice":"g5","id":null,"timestamp":1776644561423}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G6\n    \n      \"Pattern of the Week\" deep-dive blog · SEO gold\n      Long-form written pattern essay published weekly to /blog. 2000-3000 word treatment — history, variations, case study, code in 5 languages, interview questions. SEO-optimized for developers Googling \"what is the X pattern\". Blog infrastructure already exists at /blog.\n      Opus writes. 36 patterns × weekly = 9 months of content queued. Each post = 4-6h Opus. SEO flywheel.","choice":"g6","id":null,"timestamp":1776644563348}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G7\n    \n      Accessibility: beyond compliance · actually delightful on screen readers\n      Most technical sites check accessibility boxes. Architex goes further: canvas UML has a full narrative text mode generated per pattern (\"The Factory Method pattern consists of 5 classes. Creator, an abstract class, defines factoryMethod()...\"). VoiceOver / NVDA users get a first-class experience, not a degraded one.\n      Already ScreenReaderView.tsx exists in your codebase — extend to all modes. Full keyboard canvas (navigate UML classes via tab). ~15h. Dyslexia-friendly font option, high-contrast mode polish. Also expands legal/enterprise market.","choice":"g7","id":null,"timestamp":1776644565515}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G8\n    \n      Easter eggs · hidden delights that reward curiosity\n      Small secret achievements that reward exploration:\n      \n        🥚 Code poet — discover 3 easter-egg comments hidden in lesson code\n        ⌨️ Konami master — ↑↑↓↓←→←→BA unlocks a hidden \"Beta Tester\" badge\n        🌙 Night owl — learn past 2am → private \"midnight architect\" stamp\n        🔮 Perfect recall — 20 FSRS reviews in a row rated \"Easy\"\n        🧘 The Singleton life — use ONE pattern for 3 consecutive drills (thematic)\n      \n      ~4-6h content + triggers. Makes the product feel alive. Users talking about secret achievements = organic word-of-mouth.","choice":"g8","id":null,"timestamp":1776644566448}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G9\n    \n      BYOK · bring your own Claude key\n      Pro users can paste their own Anthropic API key → all AI features run on their budget. Lower your cost, they get unlimited AI usage. Win-win. Stored encrypted, never logged.\n      Settings flow + server-side encryption. ~6h. Important for enterprise/senior dev adoption who want cost isolation.","choice":"g9","id":null,"timestamp":1776644567756}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G10\n    \n      Architex API · devs build on top\n      Public API for `/api/patterns/:id`, `/api/problems/:id`, `/api/grade` (submit UML, get score). Enables external tools to consume Architex content. Textbook publishers embed. Bootcamps integrate. Universities license. Platform play.\n      Already has most endpoints — just need public documentation + API keys + rate limiting per key. Stripe-style dev portal. ~20h. Long-term moat.","choice":"g10","id":null,"timestamp":1776644568689}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G11\n    \n      \"Architex for teams\" · bootcamp / classroom mode\n      One account manages N students. Teacher dashboard shows cohort progress. Assign patterns as homework. Review student drills. Leaderboard within-cohort only (not public). Pricing: $X/seat/month.\n      Uses existing user/tier/org structure. ~30h for basic teacher dashboard. B2B revenue channel.","choice":"g11","id":null,"timestamp":1776644581439}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G12\n    \n      Alumni showcase · \"people who finished all 36\"\n      Public page listing users who achieved all 36 Mastered. Opt-in. LinkedIn/GitHub link allowed. Becomes a recruiter hunting ground. Badge on their profile: \"Architex Certified · 36/36\".\n      Powerful career incentive. Completing = verifiable credential visible to recruiters. ~8h page. Opt-in only.","choice":"g12","id":null,"timestamp":1776644582114}
