{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"L1\n    \n      Resizable panels everywhere · drag-to-resize sidebar/canvas/properties\n      Currently panel widths are fixed. Engineers want control — give them drag handles at panel borders. Preferences persist per-user. Mini-map auto-positions. Your stack already has react-resizable-panels.\n      ~4h. Library already in deps.","choice":"l1","id":null,"timestamp":1776644840015}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"L2\n    \n      Collapsible panels · one-click hide sidebar / properties for focus\n      Hit the chevron → sidebar slides away, canvas expands to claim space. Same for properties panel. Keybindings: ⌘[ collapse sidebar, ⌘] collapse properties. Muscle-memory from VS Code.\n      ~3h. Chevron UI + state persistence.","choice":"l2","id":null,"timestamp":1776644842964}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"L3\n    \n      Pattern tabs · browser-style tabs for open patterns/problems\n      Open Singleton. Click Observer — opens in a new tab. Switch between tabs without losing scroll/state. ⌘W closes. Pros familiar pattern from VS Code / Figma.\n      \n        ● Singleton ×\n        Observer ×\n        Parking Lot ×\n        +\n      \n      ~10h. Each tab persists canvas state.","choice":"l3","id":null,"timestamp":1776644849757}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"L3\n    \n      Pattern tabs · browser-style tabs for open patterns/problems\n      Open Singleton. Click Observer — opens in a new tab. Switch between tabs without losing scroll/state. ⌘W closes. Pros familiar pattern from VS Code / Figma.\n      \n        ● Singleton ×\n        Observer ×\n        Parking Lot ×\n        +\n      \n      ~10h. Each tab persists canvas state.","choice":"l3","id":null,"timestamp":1776644851815}
